Under some circumstances (I can not exactly describe them, but look at the example-code) the map ASMExecEnv#vmTypeOperations uses other instances of ASMEMFModelElement representing Ecore-objects (like EClass) as keys than that ones you get with ASMOclAny#getType(). 
The problem occures, when both are equal (for example, both represent the same EClass), but are different instances ("!="). In that case, the VM doesn't find any valid operations for the getType()-type, because of the lack of overriding the hashCode() in ASMEMFModelElement there are no registered operations for that instance.
This results in different "could not find operation"-errors, which are sometimes followed by an EmptyStackException.


